  "html": "<p><strong>Status:</strong> Historical context and dormant design horizon. This section is not part of the current MVP and is not a roadmap commitment.</p>\n<p>OpenAgents has explored a much larger system than the product shipping today. The current product is the local-first OpenAgents Desktop Codex workroom. The topics here explain earlier experiments and design ideas without presenting them as available features.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-read-this-section\"><a class=\"docs-heading-anchor\" href=\"#how-to-read-this-section\">How to read this section</a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Historical</strong> means OpenAgents previously researched, demonstrated, or implemented some version of the idea.</li>\n<li><strong>Removed</strong> means the accepted Desktop MVP deliberately excludes it and its executable product path was retired.</li>\n<li><strong>Dormant design horizon</strong> means useful contracts or lessons remain, but no active product-expansion lane exists.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A topic moves back into active development only through a new, bounded owner decision and issue. Old code, demos, transcripts, or tests do not create that authority.</p>\n<h2 id=\"topics\"><a class=\"docs-heading-anchor\" href=\"#topics\">Topics</a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/future/marketplaces\">Marketplaces</a> covers agent, plugin, data, compute, and accepted-outcome markets.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/future/nostr\">Nostr</a> covers identity, registries, storage, and open job protocols.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/future/bitcoin-and-lightning\">Bitcoin and Lightning</a> covers L402, wallets, tipping, payouts, and settlement experiments.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/docs/future/remote-workrooms\">Remote workrooms</a> covers Fleet, mobile supervision, managed targets, and portable sessions.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"source-boundary\"><a class=\"docs-heading-anchor\" href=\"#source-boundary\">Source boundary</a></h2>\n<p>This section is a curated reading guide based on the canonical Sol roadmap and the public build-in-public transcript index. Transcripts record what was explored at the time; they do not prove present availability. The roadmap and current product evidence take precedence.</p>\n",
